50|$|No. 205 Group {{was made}} {{responsible}} for supervising the <b>evacuation</b> <b>programme</b> for the RAF from the Canal Zone from 1953. Air Vice Marshal Barnett moved his rear headquarters over to Cyprus in October 1955, and Abu Sueir {{was the last}} station {{to be handed over}} to the Egyptians. This was despite the fact that Abu Sueir and Fanara were the two bases to be retained, to be maintained by civilian contractors. Abu Sueir was handed over to Egypt on 14 April 1956, and the group was disbanded the following day.|$|R
